[ENH] Adds ability to calculate dense microarray expression

Adds `dense` keyword argument to `abagen.get_expression_data()` which ensures that every ROI in provided atlas image is matched to a microarray sample (versus matching samples to ROIs, often resulting in ROIs with no expression information).
[TEST] Adds tests and fixes linting issues

[ENH] Adds parquet for faster file IO

Loading microarray + pacall data took a long time due to the large file
sizes. This commit adds support for converting those data to parquet
files for _significantly_ faster loading times. The conversion is, if
desired, done during data download (i.e., `abagen.fetch_microarray()`);
this conversion can be turned off by providing the `convert=False`
keyword argument to the call.

Moreover, attempting to load either microarray or pacall data using the
`abagen.io` functions will also check if a parquet version of the file
exists and (1) attempt to convert the CSV to a parquet file, if it
doesn't exist or (2) load the parquet file. This functionality can be
turned off by providing the `parquet=False` keyword argument to the `io`
functions.

[ENH] Improves IO handling of DataFrames

All `abagen.io` functions now check if a dataframe was passed instead of
a string; if so, a copy of the dataframe is returned. If neither a
string nor a dataframe is passed, a TypeError is raised instead.

[ENH] Adds `abagen.processing` functions

New functions for better processing, including intensity-based filtering

representative probes, probe filtering based on anatomical regions, and

Begins to integrate functions from `abagen.processing` in primary
workflows found in `abagen.allen`. Also moves helper functions to

[FIX] Resolves dataframe formatting issue

Loading data using the `abagen.io` functions that rely (optionally) on
parquet when parquet isn't installed resulted in some errors. That is,
the columns and index name of `microarray` and `pacall` data weren't
being set correctly if the parquet version of these files didn't exist,
resulting in indexing errors during a call to `get_expression_data()`.

Since parquet is _supposed_ to be optional, this is obviously undesired.
This commit ensures that columns / index names are set correctly
regardless of loading with parquet or pandas.

[FIX] Fixes correction in `remove_distance()`

The `remove_distance()` function in `abagen.correct` previously
considered cortical-subcortical and subcortical-cortical connections
separately when regressing distance, despite an inability to appreciate
directed connections. This patch ensures that distance is regressed from
all cortical-subcortical connections regardless of directionality at the
same time.

[FIX] Catches AttributeError w/pandas fastparquet

If the installed version of pandas is too old then trying to call
`pd.io.parquet.get_engine('fastparquet')` fails with an AttributeError
because pandas.io does not have a parquet module. Since all the parquet
nonsense is optional (and only really a small improvement in terms of
load-time...), it doesn't make sense to pin the new pandas dependency,
so we're just gonna go with catching the warning and ignoring parquet.

[FIX] Error in lr_mirror

When the function got updated somehow the hemisphere updating got
messed up. This fixes the issue so that mirrored data are now
treated appropriately.

[REF] Update mouse data cache location

Uses default $HOME/abagen-data instead of site-packages

[ENH] Adds surfaces modules

Includes functions for generating graphs from surface geometry files
and calculating shortest paths / distances on surface graphs

[REF] Give AtlasTree surface graphs

AtlasTree now has a reference to surface triangles and graphs for use
in calculating e.g., shortest paths on the surface

[ENH] Method for matching whole label

Adds new `fill_label()` method for `AtlasTree` that, given a label
and an annotation dataframe (or similar), assigns every coordinate
in the label a nearby sample.

[REF] 1-index sample_id in abagen.io

So that they can more easily be used with AtlasTree

[REF] Overhaul `exact` matching

Major overhaul to how "inexact" matching is done, with the option
to specify the (old) centroid-based matching or a new distance-
weighted interpolation matching. Method is specified via the new
parameter `missing` (which will replace `exact` at a later date).

[ENH] Working function for dense maps

Adds working function to generate dense (interpolated) maps of
specific genes, given an output space / mask. Uses K-nearest
neighbors regression to compute the output.

[TEST] Updating exact param in tests

Changed to missing

[DOC] Update docs on exact parameter

Changed to reflect new missing parameter

[FIX] Match closest centroid bug

With no atlas_info, matching wasn't being done to centroids

[FIX] Fix column name

When `missing='centroids'` generated dataframe column name was being
unset

[DOC] Fix sample_id doctest

Sample IDs are 1-indexed now to better work with AtlasTree()

[FIX] Bug in get_graph_distance

When providing `labels` it was collapsing over all dimensions

[REF] Weighted average for centroids

Refactors `missing='centroids'` to use the weighted average across
donors rather than simply taking the single closest sample

[REF] Negative tolerance for surfaces

Will make it so matching is constrained by an exact mm amount rather
than a s.d. threshold

[FIX] Fixes bug in 'average' probesel

The index was being renamed and breaking everything

[FIX] Fix labeltable for surface atlas

Some labeltables have bilateral labels, yielding atlas info dataframe
that is 2x length it should be. This only keeps labels relevant to
each hemisphere

[DOC] Update expression.rst

Fixes mislabelled regions in getting dense expression data section

[REF] Changes coords in samples_in_mask

Remove the call to drop_mismatch_samples() in get_samples_in_mask()
which was causing coordinates to be out-of-alignment with returned
expression data when donor-specific masks were provided
[FIX] Fixes errors from coords as df

[FIX] Fixes tol=0 error w/donor atlases

Addresses error where two donors had no matched samples when setting
tolerance=0 and using donor-specific atlases

[FIX] Fixes errors from return_donor dict

Surprise! Changing the API introduced some errors that tests caught
(thankfully). This should resolve most things

[FIX] Fixes logger error w/reports

The returned reports were true but because we were calling
images.coerce_atlas_to_dict() multiple times the logger was being
called multiple times to report what type of atlas was provided.

[ENH] Re-orient images before zero lh

When providing images to images.leftify_atlas() if the images weren't
in RAS orientation then the return atlas was not correctly zeroed out.
This modification re-orients the atlas, zeros out the appropriate
areas, then re-re-orients the atlas back to its original format.

[REF] Handle atlases w/decimal vox sizes

Adds improved handling of atlases with non-integer voxel sizes

[FIX] Pandas Compatibility (#214)

Fixing stuff due to pandas updates. Currently tests are breaking. More changes to follow.
